__NOTOC__ bool '''CheckActorState''' (int ''tid'', str ''statename'' [, bool ''exact'']);
== Usage == Checks to see if the actor with the matching [[TID]] has the specified [[Actor states|state]]. If ''tid'' is 0, the check is performed on the activator of the script.
=== Parameters === *''tid'': The TID of the actor on which to perform the state check. *''statename'': The state to check for. *''exact'': Specifies whether or not partial state name matches are accepted (see {{c|[[SetActorState]]}} for more information and an example). Default is {{c|{{const|false}}}}.
=== Return value === The function returns ''true'' if a matching state is found, otherwise it returns ''false''.
== Examples == {{noexamples}}
